# Feature Syntax

## Basic Syntax
   - Using all exsiting json syntax highlight as basis 
   - Add settings config of `.ifcx` file extension for user, or default association with file extension

```json
"files.associations": {
  "*.ifcx": "json"
}

## Special Syntax Highlighting
  - Highlight each schemas item's name, like "bsi::name", "bsi::ifc5::alpha::class" or "bsi::ifc5::alpha::properties::isexternal"

```json
{
  "header": {
    "version": "ifcx_alpha",
    "author": "authorname",
    "timestamp": "time string"
  },
  "schemas": {
    "bsi::name": {
      "value": {
        "dataType": "String"
      }
    },
    "bsi::ifc5::alpha::class": {
      "value": {
        "dataType": "Object",
        "objectRestrictions": {
          "values": {
            "code": {
              "dataType": "String"
            },
            "uri": {
              "dataType": "String"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "bsi::ifc5::alpha::properties::isexternal": {
      "value": {
        "dataType": "Boolean"
      }
    },
  }
}
```
